In this article, the White House Office of the Press Secretary provides a readout of a call between President Obama and Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu. The call was made to offer condolences and assistance following a terrorist attack in Bulgaria that targeted Israeli tourists. The President strongly condemned the attack and expressed support for Israel during this difficult time. He also pledged to provide whatever assistance is necessary to identify and bring the perpetrators to justice. The President reaffirmed the United States' commitment to Israel's security and emphasized the deep friendship and solidarity between the two countries.